================================================================================
Third-party dependencies
================================================================================

`doc-rag` builds on the following open-source projects. Their respective
licenses apply to copies redistributed as part of this project (e.g. in
Docker images or deployment archives).

This list covers the project's declared dependencies and the optional
extras commonly installed alongside it. It is not exhaustive of
transitive dependencies — `pip show <package>` is authoritative for any
specific install.

Required runtime dependencies
-----------------------------

  numpy               — BSD-3-Clause
                        https://numpy.org/
  PyYAML              — MIT
                        https://pyyaml.org/
  filetype            — MIT
                        https://github.com/h2non/filetype.py
  python-docx         — MIT
                        https://github.com/python-openxml/python-docx
  tqdm                — MPL-2.0 AND MIT
                        https://github.com/tqdm/tqdm
  docling             — MIT
                        https://github.com/docling-project/docling
                        (IBM Research; the sole PDF backend since v2.0)

Docling — bundled ML model weights
----------------------------------

`docling` downloads ML model weights on first parse. Each upstream
distributes the weights under its own license; doc-rag does not
redistribute them. Reproduce them locally and consult the upstream
project for the authoritative terms:

  TableFormer        — IBM Research; see
                       https://github.com/docling-project/docling-ibm-models
                       (table-structure recognition)
  DocLayout-YOLO     — see https://github.com/opendatalab/DocLayout-YOLO
                       (page-layout detection)
  RapidOCR           — Apache-2.0; see
                       https://github.com/RapidAI/RapidOCR
                       (OCR for scanned/embedded-image pages)

