================================================================================
License compatibility notes
================================================================================

`doc-rag` is licensed under MIT. All declared runtime dependencies are
under MIT, BSD, Apache-2.0, or MPL-2.0 licenses — fully compatible.

The legacy `.doc` parser path shells out to `antiword` (GPL-2.0) as a
separate subprocess. Calling a GPL binary as an external process does
not impose GPL obligations on doc-rag's own code, but redistributors
should respect antiword's terms when shipping the binary alongside.

History
-------

doc-rag versions before 2.0.0 were licensed under AGPL-3.0-or-later
because the default PDF backend at the time was PyMuPDF (AGPL-3.0).
PyMuPDF was removed in v2.0 in favour of Docling (MIT), and the project
relicensed to MIT in the same release. Old releases keep their AGPL
notice; v2.0 onwards is MIT.
